"{\"uid\": \"theconversation.com-astronomy-olympics-is-being-hosted-in-africa-for-the-first-time-4-big-talking-points-236150\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Distinguished Professor at the College of Science, Engineering and Technology, University of South Africa  James Okwe Chibueze does not work for, consult, own shares in or receive funding from any company or organisation that would benefit from this article, and has disclosed no relevant affiliations beyond their academic appointment.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 336, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"University of South Africaprovides funding as a partner of The Conversation AFRICA.\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 423, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 399, \"end\": 415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1372309305645465e-25, \"text\": \"The Conversation\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q11424\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Conversation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"View all partners  https://doi.org/10.64628/AAJ.yr4jn6xej  Share article  Print article  Cutting-edge telescopes, gravitational waves, black holes and our solar system's central star, the Sun, are just a few of the topics that will be on the table in Cape Town, South Africa, for an event that's a scientific version of the Olympic Games - though the world's leading astronomy researchers in attendance will be showcasing their brains rather than their brawn.\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.23213121998297e-44, \"text\": \"Sun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\"}, {\"begin\": 676, \"end\": 685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cape_Town\", \"score\": 0.6440612511917297, \"rank\": 0.5526473579177003, \"text\": \"Cape Town\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cape_Town\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cape_Town\"}, {\"begin\": 687, \"end\": 699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.107131372962577e-17, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Astronomical Union (IAU) was established in 1919 and held its first General Assembly in Rome, Italy, in 1922.\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 1013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 917, \"end\": 922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999984048580689, \"rank\": 1.5951442290293567e-06, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 924, \"end\": 927, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Astronomical_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.979671788929992e-42, \"text\": \"IAU\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Astronomical_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Astronomical_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 972, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_General_Assembly\", \"score\": 0.9999999993424353, \"rank\": 6.567426704939861e-10, \"text\": \"General Assembly\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_General_Assembly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_General_Assembly\"}, {\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 996, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9351548123995297, \"rank\": 0.06840635578483724, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}, {\"begin\": 998, \"end\": 1003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9999677313644076, \"rank\": 3.2216957287023764e-05, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These assemblies, held every three years, are a chance for the organisation's members and affiliates to meet in person, and for researchers to share their work with their peers from around the globe.\", \"from\": 1014, \"to\": 1213, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The32nd General Assembly, which kicks off on 6 August and concludes nine days later, marks the meeting's first outing in Africa.\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1223, \"end\": 1239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_General_Assembly\", \"score\": 0.9999999993424353, \"rank\": 6.567426704939861e-10, \"text\": \"General Assembly\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_General_Assembly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_General_Assembly\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a significant milestone for the continent; astronomy has grown and strengthened tremendously over the past decade.\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1466, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is largely, though not entirely, a result of South Africa's status as co-host, with Australia, of what will be the world's largest radio telescope, the Square Kilometre Array (SKA), operated and managed by theSquare Kilometre Array Observatory.\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1518, \"end\": 1530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.107131372962577e-17, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 1557, \"end\": 1566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999999975325409, \"rank\": 2.335592589578991e-09, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its first phase is set for completion in 2027; its precursor, the MeerKAT telescope, is already makinghuge contributionsto both South African and international science.\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Additional SKA dishes will be located in eight other African countries: Ghana, Zambia, Madagascar, Botswana, Namibia, Kenya, Mauritius and Mozambique.\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 2037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1959, \"end\": 1964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ghana\", \"score\": 0.9999999997749001, \"rank\": 2.2498080375491138e-10, \"text\": \"Ghana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ghana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ghana\"}, {\"begin\": 1966, \"end\": 1972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia\", \"score\": 0.9999999960618879, \"rank\": 3.9379656465501995e-09, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia\"}, {\"begin\": 1974, \"end\": 1984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madagascar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.573869963670849e-14, \"text\": \"Madagascar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madagascar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madagascar\"}, {\"begin\": 1986, \"end\": 1994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.065843447556034e-12, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 1996, \"end\": 2003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Namibia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.679517816260244e-15, \"text\": \"Namibia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Namibia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Namibia\"}, {\"begin\": 2005, \"end\": 2010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1527748897187652e-13, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 2012, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mauritius\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.1315233719250168e-12, \"text\": \"Mauritius\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mauritius\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mauritius\"}, {\"begin\": 2026, \"end\": 2036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mozambique\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.094182456014434e-13, \"text\": \"Mozambique\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mozambique\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mozambique\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:MeerKAT: the South African radio telescope that's transformed our understanding of the cosmos  As an astronomer - and the member of the assembly's national organising committee tasked with coordinating its scientific activities - I am very excited to see this meeting come to the African continent for the first time.\", \"from\": 2039, \"to\": 2366, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The programme is packed withsymposia, focus meetings dedicated toa variety of astronomical subjects, poster presentations and more.\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, I have chosen just four of the scientific topics under discussion during the assembly.\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The astronomy world rejoiced on 25 December 2021 when theJames Webb Space Telescopewas successfully launched.\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2657, \"end\": 2661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_E._Webb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0428471380063738e-23, \"text\": \"Webb\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_E._Webb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_E._Webb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Months later the telescope went into testing and verification phases; it is now in full science operations mode and producing discoveries at an astonishing rate.\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2866, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What makes it especially effective is that it offers astronomers the high sensitivity - the ability to detect faint, distant objects - required to study the early universe.\", \"from\": 2867, \"to\": 3039, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the assembly's symposia, titled \\\"The first chapters of our cosmic history with JWST\\\" features some of the new results in the exploration of the early universe, when the first stars and galaxies were formed.\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3127, \"end\": 3131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"JWST\", \"types\": [\"Q2133344\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is fascinating for astronomers and non-astronomers alike: we are all interested in knowing whether there is another planet like ours out there, and the James Webb Space Telescope has already been used to discover many new exoplanets (planets that orbit outside our own solar system).\", \"from\": 3256, \"to\": 3544, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3413, \"end\": 3439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"James Webb Space Telescope\", \"types\": [\"Q2133344\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Webb_Space_Telescope\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Could any of these planets be habitable for humans?\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3596, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We may have answers sooner than we expected as the telescope continues its remarkable work.\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3688, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Neutral hydrogenis the most abundant element in the universe and is an essential part of the makeup of galaxies in the universe.\", \"from\": 3690, \"to\": 3818, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When the spin direction of the electron in the hydrogen atom flips, radio emissions are produced.\", \"from\": 3819, \"to\": 3916, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These emissions can be detected by radio telescopes and are crucial for understanding the distribution and kinematics (motion) of gases in galaxies.\", \"from\": 3917, \"to\": 4065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MeerKAT, a precursor to the SKA, is already producing groundbreaking neutral hydrogen science because it is currently the most sensitive telescope for neutral hydrogen observations.\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4095, \"end\": 4098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Square_Kilometre_Array\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.860053603273879e-83, \"text\": \"SKA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Square_Kilometre_Array\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Square_Kilometre_Array\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:Africa's MeerKAT 'first light' images have blown all expectations  Of course, a project the size and scope of the SKA will not only be discussed in one or two sessions.\", \"from\": 4250, \"to\": 4428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4374, \"end\": 4377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Square_Kilometre_Array\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.860053603273879e-83, \"text\": \"SKA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Square_Kilometre_Array\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Square_Kilometre_Array\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An entirefocus meetingat the assembly is dedicated to delving into the history of astronomy in South Africa and how it evolved to the point that it was chosen to host the world's biggest radio astronomy project.\", \"from\": 4429, \"to\": 4640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4524, \"end\": 4536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.107131372962577e-17, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:How visionary scientist Bernie Fanaroff put African astronomy on the map  It's been nine years since scientists announced that they had, for the first time ever,detected gravitational waves.\", \"from\": 4642, \"to\": 4842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4676, \"end\": 4691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bernard_L._Fanaroff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bernie Fanaroff\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bernard_L._Fanaroff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bernard_L._Fanaroff\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This provided clear evidence to supportAlbert Einstein's prediction, a century earlier, thatgravitational waves existed.\", \"from\": 4843, \"to\": 4963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4889, \"end\": 4897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 6.454651023687055e-13, \"text\": \"Einstein\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Albert_Einstein\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since that first confirmation a variety of new science has emerged in the field of gravitational wave astrophysics.\", \"from\": 4965, \"to\": 5080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Astronomers are able to explore our observable universe using not just electromagnetic waves, but gravitational waves - \\\"ripples\\\" in space-time - too.\", \"from\": 5081, \"to\": 5231, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of these results will be showcased ina symposiumat the general assembly.\", \"from\": 5232, \"to\": 5309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Sun, the central star of our solar system, is the nearest stellar laboratory available to scientists studying the true nature and environmental impact of solar winds and coronal mass ejections, otherwise referred to as space storms that cause aurora.\", \"from\": 5311, \"to\": 5565, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5315, \"end\": 5318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.23213121998297e-44, \"text\": \"Sun\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stars of masses eight times or more than that of the Sun are referred to as massive stars.\", \"from\": 5567, \"to\": 5657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Such high-mass stars evolve faster than their low-mass counterparts.\", \"from\": 5658, \"to\": 5726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They end their lives in an explosive process, a supernova, and leave behind a fast-spinning neutron star, known as a pulsar.\", \"from\": 5727, \"to\": 5851, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:In a rare sighting, astronomers observe burst of activity as a massive star forms  One of the focus meetings will concentrate onexploring new resultsthat bridge the gap between massive stars, supernovae and transients from pulsars.\", \"from\": 5853, \"to\": 6094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Understanding the full evolutionary sequence of massive stars is key to understanding the evolution of galaxies since massive stars influence the chemical composition, structure and morphology of their host galaxy.\", \"from\": 6095, \"to\": 6309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anda symposiumhas been dedicated to considering recent advances in solar observations.\", \"from\": 6310, \"to\": 6396, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The general assembly is also a chance for groups of astronomers to organise side meetings.\", \"from\": 6398, \"to\": 6488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the science under discussion at these meetings in 2024 includes theEvent Horizon Telescope, a global array which is used for black hole imaging, and theAfrican Millimetre Telescopein Namibia.\", \"from\": 6489, \"to\": 6688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6680, \"end\": 6687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Namibia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.679517816260244e-15, \"text\": \"Namibia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Namibia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Namibia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other meetings will focus on the South African Radio Astronomy Observatory and how to keep night skies dark and quiet for optimal radio astronomy.\", \"from\": 6689, \"to\": 6835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6736, \"end\": 6751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_astronomy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Radio Astronomy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_astronomy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Radio_astronomy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2025,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 6837, \"to\": 6891, \"entities\": []}]}"